Kitty Power's Matchmaker proves that even the simplest game mechanic can be incredibly addictive when given the right wrapping.  Masquerading as a dating game, KP Matchmaker is actually a set of memory mini-games, encouraging you to pay attention to all the small details and trying to pair people based on their similarities in either interests or personalities.  As you progress in the game you have to balance satisfying your clients with being able to complete the mini-games, as more affluent clients desire higher-end restaurants which in means more difficult and chance-based mini-games.   Kitty Power serves as your guide and commentator, making small humorous, slightly salacious comments on the dates and situations, and gives you helpful hints for the game, making the experience funny, charming and light-hearted, but with a lecherous twist.   If you like light strategy, management games, memory based puzzles or untraditional dating sims I recommend giving this game a small amount of your time and money. So far I've had a hard time pulling myself away from helping just -one- more client..
